  "pages": 368,
  "note": "Wonderfully written, especially and predominantly as for the first half of the book; as a whole it feels complete but I just don't see too much value in it. Most of it is well constructed but apart from revolving around a taboo as a centerpoint it just does not deliver anything above what a typical novel should and does."
